title.gco:CharacterString: Oil and Gas Wells in the United States, 2011

abstract.gco:CharacterString: This layer shows the locations of oil and gas wells in the United States. Information in this layer is based on data provided by numerous sources in a variety of digital formats, collected at the state or county level.

purpose.gco:CharacterString: The purpose of this file is to combine multiple well data sources into one national file.

credit.gco:CharacterString: Hart Energy Publishing. (2012) Oil and Gas Wells in the United States, 2011. Hart Energy Publishing.

otherConstraints.gco:CharacterString: Access is granted to Stanford University affiliates only. Affiliates are limited to current faculty, staff and students. Unauthorized use, disclosure or reproduction is prohibited.

title.gco:CharacterString: Oil and Gas Wells GIS Data: United States

environmentDescription.gco:CharacterString: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.1.0.3035

supplementalInformation.gco:CharacterString: This release is intended to replace all previous datasets.

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: The number assigned to wells by either the American Petroleum Institute or another regulatory agency.
Internal feature number.
Feature geometry.
State API code assigned by the API.
5 digit well unique identifier. Availability depends the state.
Country code
Code representing the presence of directional drilling. Availability depends on state.
Used to distinguish between separate operations in a single well. Availability depends on state.
United States FIPS code for the state within which the well was drilled.
Well name; may consist of a combination of the well’s operator, well number, and lease name.
Well operator company name.
Well type code. Used to differentiate between oil, gas, water, and injection wells. Well type codes may differ by state or include references to well status.
Well status code. Used to represent the status of an oil, gas, water, or injection well. Well status codes may differ by state.
Township direction: N = North; S = South
Township direction: N = North; S = South

Range Direction: E = East; W = West

Producing formation.
Spud date. Date of initial drilling.
Completion date. Date a well is fitted for production.
Permit date.
Production date. Date a well begins production.
Plug date.
Well depth proposed by operator. Units in feet unless otherwise noted.
Measured total well depth. Units in feet unless otherwise noted.
Total plug back depth. Units in feet unless otherwise noted.
Ground level elevation in feet. Units in feet unless otherwise noted.
Kelly Bushing's elevation in feet. Units in feet unless otherwise noted.
Derrick Floor elevation in feet. Units in feet unless otherwise noted.
